column6: the idea of distributed/local gardens is great, the only problem is that sometimes it's too "local" (the attendees prefer not to switch to english and you don't have the impression to take/be part of an international workshop). So one option to avoid this prolem could be to organize "along-the-border" gardens: 2/3 or more countries organize a common garden in a town easy to reach from all of them !
